We hope this peek into our process gives clarity to Boki's journey. Look out for more character reveals coming up.

A World of dreams, adventure, and escapism awaits! üå± https://t.co/p5sqMJi7lN

The Boki team's ethos is two-fold: build out the Boki according to the values of Web3 and develop the Boki storyline, characters, and lore from the ground-up. We work WITH the community, not parallel to it.

Now, Boki rests comfortably in Otter's wallet, ready for his Adventure across the World of Boki to become a Dreamer AND Adventurer and‚Äîby some miracle‚Äîfind his long lost parents.

As opposed to hand-picking Boki, we opted for a true Web3 process of revealing and acquisition.

Thankfully, our Discord community member Elise revealed they had in fact minted and revealed Boki (Boki 355). Our journey wrapped up, but now came the time for purchasing Boki. Boki founder Otter reached out to Elise, worked out a deal, and acquired Boki. A smooth end! https://t.co/PXxfg5CX5x

Fast forward to reveal day. Despite our hopes, Boki did not appear in our team wallets. The journey to find and acquire him was on! Due to filtering issues, we attempted to track him down through our collection on OpenSea. Wading through 7,777 mints is no small task. https://t.co/hJ7bSNCPsT

Some context: the Boki team used Chainlink VRF tech to randomize the reveal for the collection. This meant that we had no control over which Boki revealed in our wallets. We introduced Boki, our mascot, previously, but we had no direct way to mint him. The odds were low.

Yesterday, we announced our first official character and our mascot: Boki. But Boki simply didn't appear in our team wallet; the Boki team went on an Adventure of our own to track him down among our 7,777 mints and acquire him for our World.

This is the story of acquiring Boki. https://t.co/y2sSvkhXsS

Now, Boki dreams about the mystery of his parents. Are they still out there? Did they find the Second Seed? Where are they now?

Sometimes Boki's thirst for outside knowledge conflicted with his studies, but he held fast in his love of learning. He made friends with his fellow Boki and creatures, growing up alongside a young sheep, naming her Wooly, and forging a lifelong bond.
Inspired by his parents, Boki dedicated his childhood to poring over the history of their World. He refined his parents‚Äô technology and built a portable map accessible to all Adventurers.

Boki's parents broke tradition and followed in the Adventurers‚Äô footsteps, determined to see their entire World themselves. They left Boki in the care of their home‚Äôs Boki Sage. They were never seen again.

Boki is his parents' only son, named after their World and the Boki people. They loved Boki so very much, but adventure called to them, including a rumor of a new Seed‚Äîthe Second Seed‚Äîgrowing beyond the world they knew.
